151
00:11:13,881 --> 00:11:16,967
I had no sense of sound or smell.

152
00:11:17,051 --> 00:11:21,263
That dark room
was the definition of darkness.

153
00:11:21,347 --> 00:11:23,057
I only spent an hour there at first.

154
00:11:23,140 --> 00:11:25,851
Even that felt like an eternity.

155
00:11:25,935 --> 00:11:29,313
But I was able to endure it.
There was no way out, anyway.

156
00:11:30,231 --> 00:11:33,859
For three hours, five hours and ten hours…

157
00:11:34,860 --> 00:11:38,406
At some point,
you locked us in there all night.

158
00:11:40,741 --> 00:11:45,246
In that dark room, I had an experience
that shattered the boundaries of time.

159
00:11:48,999 --> 00:11:51,043
The lines between the past,

160
00:11:52,086 --> 00:11:54,505
present, and future began to fade away.

161
00:11:58,175 --> 00:12:00,594
Suddenly, a lot of things
started to change.

162
00:12:02,513 --> 00:12:07,017
I was who I was
but also without an identity.

163
00:12:08,436 --> 00:12:10,771
I was cut off

164
00:12:10,855 --> 00:12:13,858
but connected to everything
at the same time.

165
00:12:18,529 --> 00:12:23,159
That was probably around the time
I found the ability to control ants.

166
00:12:24,952 --> 00:12:26,829
You could say

167
00:12:30,249 --> 00:12:33,961
