And I want to

263
00:21:12,187 --> 00:21:13,939
go home every day

264
00:21:16,650 --> 00:21:18,068
holding your hand.

265
00:21:22,072 --> 00:21:22,948
Will you

266
00:21:24,866 --> 00:21:26,159
marry me?

267
00:21:47,347 --> 00:21:49,683
Se-yoon. Let's get out of here quickly.

268
00:21:51,893 --> 00:21:52,894
Se-yoon.

269
00:22:12,789 --> 00:22:14,583
Excuse me, Mister.

270
00:22:15,334 --> 00:22:16,251
Oh, okay.

271
00:22:17,794 --> 00:22:19,171
Do you need anything?

272
00:22:19,254 --> 00:22:20,589
Are you all right?

273
00:22:29,264 --> 00:22:30,307
What is this?

274
00:22:31,349 --> 00:22:32,517
It's coke tea.

275
00:22:33,268 --> 00:22:34,144
Coke what?

276
00:22:34,227 --> 00:22:36,438
It's warm coke.

277
00:22:45,572 --> 00:22:47,365
When I couldn't sleep,

278
00:22:47,449 --> 00:22:49,743
my aunt would give me warm coke
without telling grandma.

279
00:22:49,826 --> 00:22:51,620
It'll help you fall asleep.

280
00:23:06,134 --> 00:23:08,095
How does it taste?
It's pretty good, isn't it?

281
00:23:14,935 --> 00:23:17,938
Do you have nightmares often?

282
00:23:19,064 --> 00:23:20,232
Yes, most of the time.

283
00:23:20,315 --> 00:23:21,775
Since when?

284
00:23:21,858 --> 00:23:23,068
I don't know.

285
00:23:24,069 --> 00:23:25,195
I don't remember

286
00:23:26,404 --> 00:23:27,781
when they started.

287
00:23:28,949 --> 00:23:30,367
Did it start

288
00:23:30,450 --> 00:23:33,870
when you lost your baby?

289
00:23:34,621 --> 00:23:37,582
I was curious so we entered

290
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:39,793
that bedroom.

291
00:23:40,836 --> 00:23:42,003
The baby's room.

292
00:23:43,421 --> 00:23:46,550
I was going to tell you we saw the room.

293
00:23:46,633 --> 00:23:49,052
But you came home late.

294
00:23:51,012 --> 00:23:53,515
I'm sorry we didn't respect your privacy.

295
00:23:54,099 --> 00:23:55,100
No, it's all right.

296
00:23:56,059 --> 00:23:57,394
Don't let it bother you.

297
00:23:58,145 --> 00:24:00,480
Did you divorce your wife

298
00:24:01,773 --> 00:24:03,733
because you lost your baby?

299
00:24:05,527 --> 00:24:06,695
I see.

300
00:24:07,445 --> 00:24:08,947
So that's what you're curious about.

301
00:24:13,577 --> 00:24:14,828
No, that's not the reason.

302
00:24:15,829 --> 00:24:16,872
She left

303
00:24:17,998 --> 00:24:19,666
because she didn't like me anymore.

304
00:24:21,042 --> 00:24:24,713
I found out
she had a miscarriage much later.

305
00:24:24,796 --> 00:24:26,131
She informed me about it.

306
00:24:28,133 --> 00:24:30,135
There's no need for you to dwell on it.

307
00:24:32,470 --> 00:24:34,764
Your aunt asked me to care for you.

308
00:24:36,558 --> 00:24:38,476
I can see how she might have felt guilty.

309
00:24:39,561 --> 00:24:42,189
My wife and Jo Kyung-ho

310
00:24:42,981 --> 00:24:44,316
are your parents.

311
00:24:45,233 --> 00:24:46,902
So she probably got worried

312
00:24:48,320 --> 00:24:50,071
about how I would react to that.

313
00:24:52,741 --> 00:24:55,118
I wanted to ask you

314
00:24:57,204 --> 00:24:59,789
how you felt about me.

315
00:25:02,542 --> 00:25:03,585
My wife

316
00:25:05,003 --> 00:25:07,047
didn't give me an explanation
when she left.

317
00:25:07,839 --> 00:25:10,342
Which means she couldn't
stand living with me.

318
00:25:11,426 --> 00:25:15,764
So I don't think I have the right
to judge the choice she made.

319
00:25:16,806 --> 00:25:17,933
I don't think

320
00:25:18,767 --> 00:25:21,770
I should harbor any ill will
towards you either.

321
00:25:22,896 --> 00:25:24,773
I'm not sure
if that answers your question.

322
00:25:27,651 --> 00:25:28,902
It's late. So go to sleep.

323
00:25:29,736 --> 00:25:30,570
But…

324
00:25:31,571 --> 00:25:33,657
I don't think people

325
00:25:33,740 --> 00:25:36,326
leave their families without a reason.

326
00:25:37,285 --> 00:25:41,164
I think there was a deeper reason
that she couldn't tell you.

327
00:25:41,915 --> 00:25:44,417
Because she cared a lot.

328
00:25:45,043 --> 00:25:47,128
That's how it is with me and my aunt.

329
00:25:50,632 --> 00:25:51,800
You can't

330
00:25:53,843 --> 00:25:56,137
explain everything to your family.

331
00:26:22,789 --> 00:26:24,791
This is the room
for ascetic training, right?

332
00:26:24,874 --> 00:26:27,252
You hang people upside down
here every night.

333
00:26:28,086 --> 00:26:28,962
Well…

334
00:26:29,546 --> 00:26:32,257
We learned that it's important training

335
00:26:33,091 --> 00:26:35,302
to understand the true meaning
of Guru's teachings.

336
00:26:37,429 --> 00:26:39,222
I really don't like all of you.

337
00:26:40,890 --> 00:26:42,600
But you shouldn't be doing this.

338
00:26:44,602 --> 00:26:45,937
This isn't training.

339
00:26:46,980 --> 00:26:48,148
It's plainly

340
00:26:49,566 --> 00:26:50,692
torture.

341
00:26:52,986 --> 00:26:54,404
There's no other way to describe it.

342
00:27:04,831 --> 00:27:07,000
I find myself back here
after all those years.

343
00:27:11,087 --> 00:27:12,213
I told you so.

344
00:27:13,423 --> 00:27:15,675
Nothing has changed.

345
00:27:18,136 --> 00:27:19,679
-Oh my goodness.
-What to do?

346
00:27:19,763 --> 00:27:22,766
What is the meaning of this?
How dare you shout in this room!

347
00:27:33,651 --> 00:27:35,070
What do you think you're doing?

348
00:27:43,995 --> 00:27:45,914
You think what you did
will make a difference?

349
00:27:46,873 --> 00:27:49,417
Are you trying to act like a hero?

350
00:27:50,377 --> 00:27:52,420
We can install a new rope.

351
00:27:52,504 --> 00:27:54,047
What you did is meaningless.

352
00:28:16,111 --> 00:28:17,320
What are you doing?

353
00:28:22,033 --> 00:28:23,618
Stop it. Are you crazy?

354
00:28:46,015 --> 00:28:48,226
I wasn't waiting for the
rope to burn to ash.

355
00:28:49,060 --> 00:28:50,478
I wanted to show everyone that

356
00:28:50,562 --> 00:28:52,856
there is no such thing as a rope
that can't be cut down.

357
00:29:05,285 --> 00:29:06,911
Thank you for coming.

358
00:29:13,376 --> 00:29:14,627
We're done, sir.

359
00:29:19,758 --> 00:29:22,427
Would you please excuse me?

360
00:29:22,510 --> 00:29:24,012
I have to receive a guest.

361
00:29:24,554 --> 00:29:26,222
-I'm so sorry.
-That's fine.

362
00:29:39,569 --> 00:29:40,862
Now look here.

363
00:29:41,362 --> 00:29:43,281
Don't you have any manners?

364
00:29:44,032 --> 00:29:46,409
How could you come barging here

365
00:29:47,076 --> 00:29:49,037
when I'm having dinner
with family and relatives?

366
00:29:49,120 --> 00:29:50,872
And you also brought a knife with you.

367
00:29:51,414 --> 00:29:54,584
We've met before, haven't we?

368
00:29:54,667 --> 00:29:57,253
I think I met you
at the summer house before.

369
00:29:57,837 --> 00:30:01,716
I don't think we started off
on the right foot back then.

370
00:30:02,759 --> 00:30:03,885
Now I remember.

371
00:30:04,761 --> 00:30:07,305
You were with Kang Yong-tak, weren't you?

372
00:30:07,388 --> 00:30:08,431
That's right.

373
00:30:09,140 --> 00:30:12,185
I came to avenge my boss' death.

374
00:30:12,268 --> 00:30:15,438
You're not making any sense, fella.

375
00:30:16,147 --> 00:30:18,274
I'm not the one who did that to him.

376
00:30:18,358 --> 00:30:20,985
Why did you come to
the wrong place for vengeance?

377
00:30:21,069 --> 00:30:25,532
I just do business with the Youngjin Sect.

378
00:30:32,205 --> 00:30:33,748
Did you know

379
00:30:34,582 --> 00:30:37,001
that the place where your boss died

380
00:30:37,961 --> 00:30:40,380
is where the Youngjin Sect gather to pray?

381
00:30:41,673 --> 00:30:45,301
And the representative who leads
the Youngjin Sect is a sly fox.

382
00:30:45,385 --> 00:30:48,680
Objectively speaking,

383
00:30:48,763 --> 00:30:50,265
it's the representative's fault

384
00:30:51,140 --> 00:30:52,976
that your boss died like that.

385
00:30:53,560 --> 00:30:55,562
So if you want revenge,

386
00:30:55,645 --> 00:30:57,981
you should go after him.

387
00:31:00,942 --> 00:31:03,528
Hey, untie his hands.

388
00:31:04,529 --> 00:31:06,531
You tied his hands so tight

389
00:31:06,614 --> 00:31:08,533
that they're turning purple.

390
00:31:12,662 --> 00:31:15,290
If you want to accomplish a lot in life,

391
00:31:15,373 --> 00:31:17,709
you need to be able to tell
who's friend or foe.

392
00:31:17,792 --> 00:31:21,170
Seeing the spirit you have,

393
00:31:21,254 --> 00:31:23,715
I just came up with a fantastic idea.

394
00:31:23,798 --> 00:31:25,425
Would you like to hear it?

395
00:31:25,508 --> 00:31:29,596
I'm thinking about giving you
a compass that will lead you straight

396
00:31:30,763 --> 00:31:33,391
to the representative's room.

397
00:31:35,059 --> 00:31:36,394
That's my idea.

398
00:32:27,028 --> 00:32:28,404
Why did you come here?

399
00:32:29,447 --> 00:32:31,282
I've always wanted to come here.

400
00:32:32,283 --> 00:32:33,451
Where are we?

401
00:32:42,293 --> 00:32:43,461
It's just

402
00:32:44,712 --> 00:32:45,797
the school I graduated from.

403
00:33:02,480 --> 00:33:04,899
"Just the school I graduated from."

404
00:33:24,127 --> 00:33:25,169
Mister.

405
00:33:26,379 --> 00:33:27,547
Take a look at this.

406
00:33:30,049 --> 00:33:33,428
I asked Jae-young about it
and she said she didn't write it.

407
00:33:34,262 --> 00:33:37,932
And the text messages they got
weren't sent by me.

408
00:33:38,016 --> 00:33:40,685
Someone was pretending to be me.

409
00:33:41,978 --> 00:33:44,272
Who could have done this? For what?

410
00:33:46,441 --> 00:33:47,775
It was a ploy

411
00:33:47,859 --> 00:33:49,986
to lure your aunt to the cult.

412
00:33:51,112 --> 00:33:52,530
They wanted to release you

413
00:33:52,613 --> 00:33:55,742
and have your aunt take your place.

414
00:33:57,785 --> 00:33:58,703
I…

415
00:33:59,662 --> 00:34:02,749
want to go to the seven secret spots
mentioned here.

416
00:34:03,583 --> 00:34:08,337
It could help me find out
where I was held and where my aunt

417
00:34:08,421 --> 00:34:09,922
could be right now.

418
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:17,263
I don't know what this person wants
but we have to stop him.

419
00:34:17,346 --> 00:34:18,431
I want to stop this.

420
00:35:12,193 --> 00:35:13,820
GYEONGCHEON HIGH SCHOOL MAGAZINE
IS SEARCHING FOR CLUES!

421
00:35:13,903 --> 00:35:15,822
PLEASE SEND IN ANY TIPS YOU MAY HAVE

422
00:36:27,310 --> 00:36:30,188
FIRST SECRET PLACE IS THE SAJU
DEER FARM. ITS TRUE PURPOSE?

423
00:36:44,869 --> 00:36:46,037
I'm okay.

424
00:36:48,331 --> 00:36:51,500
For real. So don't cry.

425
00:37:05,389 --> 00:37:07,850
Can I see your hand?

426
00:37:30,790 --> 00:37:31,624
Successor.

427
00:37:33,084 --> 00:37:35,419
You need to stop.

428
00:37:36,712 --> 00:37:38,756
We've already made up our minds.

429
00:37:40,716 --> 00:37:42,301
You're too late.

430
00:37:43,761 --> 00:37:44,762
So

431
00:37:46,430 --> 00:37:47,682
leave us alone.

432
00:37:51,894 --> 00:37:52,895
Please.

433
00:37:55,398 --> 00:37:57,066
I won't rush anyone.

434
00:37:57,149 --> 00:37:59,360
I'll just continue staying in my place.

435
00:38:00,236 --> 00:38:02,571
So if you ever change your mind,

436
00:38:02,655 --> 00:38:03,990
come to me.

437
00:38:04,073 --> 00:38:05,658
Even if it's just once.

438
00:38:05,741 --> 00:38:06,617
Give me

439
00:38:08,035 --> 00:38:09,328
a chance.

440
00:38:54,123 --> 00:38:57,418
Thank you for coming.
I was waiting for you.

441
00:38:58,210 --> 00:39:01,505
Everyone. I am not the successor.

442
00:39:02,548 --> 00:39:06,135
So I don't have the right
to impart any teachings.

443
00:39:06,802 --> 00:39:08,137
I know that

444
00:39:09,805 --> 00:39:12,350
what I'm saying is not what you expected.

445
00:39:21,442 --> 00:39:25,905
However, I thought I could do something
even as an insignificant person.

446
00:39:31,702 --> 00:39:32,661
Everyone.

447
00:39:32,745 --> 00:39:35,206
Raise your chin. Look into my eyes.

448
00:39:35,956 --> 00:39:37,333
Please.

449
00:39:37,416 --> 00:39:38,959
And come to me and

450
00:39:39,668 --> 00:39:40,586
tell me

451
00:39:41,587 --> 00:39:42,963
your story.

452
00:39:43,589 --> 00:39:45,299
It doesn't matter what you share with me.

453
00:39:46,967 --> 00:39:48,260
Let me

454
00:39:50,054 --> 00:39:51,347
hear your voices.

455
00:40:04,610 --> 00:40:05,653
Will you

456
00:40:06,737 --> 00:40:08,489
really listen to my story?

457
00:40:10,408 --> 00:40:11,367
Yes,

458
00:40:12,618 --> 00:40:13,577
go ahead.

459
00:40:13,661 --> 00:40:14,578
Anything

460
00:40:15,371 --> 00:40:16,372
you want to say.

461
00:40:17,581 --> 00:40:18,457
I'm

462
00:40:20,126 --> 00:40:21,460
an orphan.

463
00:40:22,378 --> 00:40:23,754
My parents

464
00:40:24,922 --> 00:40:28,259
died in the 1987 terrorist attack
at Saju Station.

465
00:40:28,342 --> 00:40:30,678
I moved from one relative's house
to another.

466
00:40:30,761 --> 00:40:32,847
I never went to school.

467
00:40:43,107 --> 00:40:44,191
I think this is it.

468
00:40:59,582 --> 00:41:01,292
Do you think it'll be safe to go in?

469
00:41:04,587 --> 00:41:05,629
Is it?

470
00:41:07,965 --> 00:41:09,467
Mister.

471
00:41:09,550 --> 00:41:10,509
Oh, okay.

472
00:41:10,593 --> 00:41:13,220
-You're coming too, right?
-Of course.

473
00:41:21,353 --> 00:41:26,192
My fiancee was helping out
at her parent's shop in the station.

474
00:41:26,775 --> 00:41:29,320
She cared more about her family

475
00:41:31,155 --> 00:41:34,325
and me than herself.

476
00:41:37,077 --> 00:41:40,581
When the paramedics
retrieved grandma's body,

477
00:41:41,290 --> 00:41:43,417
they found a half-eaten taffy
in her pocket.

478
00:41:43,501 --> 00:41:44,919
She had trouble walking

479
00:41:45,628 --> 00:41:47,796
but she walked to the station

480
00:41:49,673 --> 00:41:52,301
and waited there for me
while sucking on the taffy.

481
00:41:53,135 --> 00:41:55,804
My grandma appears in my dreams a lot.

482
00:41:56,805 --> 00:41:57,765
And I'll

483
00:41:59,767 --> 00:42:00,851
speak to her while crying.

484
00:42:01,644 --> 00:42:03,938
Grandma, don't

485
00:42:05,940 --> 00:42:07,358
come to the station to pick me up.

486
00:42:08,484 --> 00:42:10,110
Please stay home.

487
00:42:12,905 --> 00:42:14,573
Grandma, please don't die.

488
00:42:17,451 --> 00:42:18,285
My husband

489
00:42:19,036 --> 00:42:20,704
worked at the train station.

490
00:42:21,288 --> 00:42:24,083
I was told he died
while saving other people

491
00:42:24,166 --> 00:42:25,334
in the station.

492
00:42:26,377 --> 00:42:29,547
Why didn't he just save himself first?

493
00:42:30,798 --> 00:42:33,884
I hate him
more than I hate the perpetrators.

494
00:42:34,510 --> 00:42:37,846
Why are you bringing up painful memories?

495
00:42:41,100 --> 00:42:43,310
We've already made up our minds.

496
00:42:45,354 --> 00:42:47,022
All of the people here

497
00:42:47,898 --> 00:42:49,775
have lost a loved one

498
00:42:51,402 --> 00:42:53,404
at Saju Station on the day of the attack.

499
00:42:54,738 --> 00:42:57,449
They've endured a pain
that's worse than dying.

500
00:42:58,951 --> 00:43:01,120
We want salvation now.

501
00:43:01,954 --> 00:43:03,581
We've been forgotten by society.

502
00:43:03,664 --> 00:43:04,999
As time went by,

503
00:43:05,874 --> 00:43:07,585
people have completely forgotten

504
00:43:08,919 --> 00:43:10,212
the painful experience

505
00:43:11,797 --> 00:43:14,675
we underwent.

506
00:43:15,676 --> 00:43:18,178
That is why we've chosen this path.

507
00:43:19,388 --> 00:43:20,431
Because Guru

508
00:43:23,350 --> 00:43:25,811
has told us he'd join us.

509
00:43:27,605 --> 00:43:28,731
He said

510
00:43:29,607 --> 00:43:31,942
he would share our pain.

511
00:43:33,068 --> 00:43:36,447
But who are you?

512
00:43:37,072 --> 00:43:40,451
What the heck can you do for us?

513
00:43:41,619 --> 00:43:44,913
You suddenly show up
and try to test our beliefs?

514
00:43:46,040 --> 00:43:46,957
Damn it.

515
00:43:50,878 --> 00:43:54,006
Why are you looking at us like that?

516
00:44:09,396 --> 00:44:10,522
I'm sorry

517
00:44:13,400 --> 00:44:14,985
for neglecting all of you.

518
00:44:16,737 --> 00:44:18,405
I wanted to forget.

519
00:44:18,989 --> 00:44:20,991
I wanted to stay as far away as possible.

520
00:44:22,743 --> 00:44:24,328
That way, I thought

521
00:44:25,954 --> 00:44:28,165
I could erase that incident.

522
00:44:29,667 --> 00:44:31,251
But I was very wrong.

523
00:44:33,420 --> 00:44:35,130
I should've met each of you.

524
00:44:36,173 --> 00:44:37,591
And listened

525
00:44:39,051 --> 00:44:40,135
to what

526
00:44:41,178 --> 00:44:42,429
you had to say.

527
00:44:43,430 --> 00:44:46,266
Someone should've apologized to you.

528
00:44:48,602 --> 00:44:50,729
An apology was in order.

529
00:44:54,274 --> 00:44:55,317
I'm sorry.

530
00:44:56,819 --> 00:44:58,028
I'm sorry for

531
00:44:59,530 --> 00:45:01,115
coming so late and forgetting.

532
00:45:03,200 --> 00:45:04,660
I'm sorry.

533
00:45:06,703 --> 00:45:08,205
I'm very sorry.

534
00:45:10,165 --> 00:45:11,542
I'm sorry.

535
00:45:12,793 --> 00:45:14,211
I'm so sorry.

536
00:45:15,295 --> 00:45:16,505
I'm sorry.

537
00:45:22,469 --> 00:45:24,012
Moon-sook told me

538
00:45:26,098 --> 00:45:27,474
that someone died here

